product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsBrow Freeze Extreme Hold Laminated-Look Sculpting Eyebrow Wax
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeBrow Freeze by Anastasia Beverly Hills is a customizable brow styling wax that lifts, tames and sculpts every hair into place for the perfect feathered-looking brows. The universal, easy-to-apply formula is mess-free and provides long-lasting, extreme hold without a stiff feel, residue or flaking.
details: DetailsBenefitsUniversal clear wax formula for all skin tones and brow colorsProvides long-lasting, extreme hold that locks brows in placeInstantly gives the look of lifted, feathered browsEasy-to-use and mess-free application (no water needed)Helps to tame unruly and coarse brow hairSets in place without a stiff feel, residue or flakingGrips to skin and hairIdeal for medium-sparse to full browsLuxe, rose gold packagingFeaturesCruelty-freeParaben-freeOil-freeItem 2574232How To UsePrior to application, make sure the Brow Freeze Applicator is clean. To remove Brow Freeze from the spoolie brush, use a small amount of warm water.Using the flat spatula end of the Brow Freeze Applicator, gently pick up a small amount of Brow Freeze.Only a small amount of Brow Freeze is needed for both brows, a little goes a long way!Close the lid and place the wax on the back of the cap.Using the spoolie brush end, swirl wax on the back of the cap to evenly distribute throughout the brush.Spin the brush to remove any excess before applying.On fresh, clean brows, brush a small amount of wax through the brow.Use upward motions and continuously brush through the brow in desired direction.Starting from front to back, use the flat spatula to press brow hairs down flat.Sculpt into place until desired shape and lift is achieved.Clean the Brow Freeze Applicator after use.Pro Tips:Keep the lid to Brow Freeze tightly sealed when not in use to maintain optimal appearance and efficacy.Remove daily with makeup remover using gentle pressure.Clean the applicator regularly with brush cleanser; warm water removes Brow Freeze from spoolie easily and quickly.IngredientsWater (Aqua) Ceteareth-30, D-Sorbitol , Propanediol, Glycerin, Phenoxyethanol Propylene Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Citric Acid, Potassium Sorbate.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Prior to application, make sure the Brow Freeze Applicator is clean. To remove Brow Freeze from the spoolie brush, use a small amount of warm water.Using the flat spatula end of the Brow Freeze Applicator, gently pick up a small amount of Brow Freeze.Only a small amount of Brow Freeze is needed for both brows, a little goes a long way!Close the lid and place the wax on the back of the cap.Using the spoolie brush end, swirl wax on the back of the cap to evenly distribute throughout the brush.Spin the brush to remove any excess before applying.On fresh, clean brows, brush a small amount of wax through the brow.Use upward motions and continuously brush through the brow in desired direction.Starting from front to back, use the flat spatula to press brow hairs down flat.Sculpt into place until desired shape and lift is achieved.Clean the Brow Freeze Applicator after use.Pro Tips:Keep the lid to Brow Freeze tightly sealed when not in use to maintain optimal appearance and efficacy.Remove daily with makeup remover using gentle pressure.Clean the applicator regularly with brush cleanser; warm water removes Brow Freeze from spoolie easily and quickly.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this again
reviews.comments: The product was so watery that when I returned it, the staff member opened it to check the product and it spilled all over his hands, the counter and my receipt

reviews.headline: Only kind I'll buy
reviews.comments: I have thin brows and this has an excellent hold on them that lasts pretty much my whole day.  I use it with the brow pomade to fill in my brows.

reviews.headline: Awful packaging
reviews.comments: I was excited to try this because i needed a new brow product until it literally would not open and ended up breaking. Micro glass shards got all over my hands, legs, and floor. I would not reccomend because you can't open it!

reviews.headline: Non holding
reviews.comments: It doesnt really hold your brows. Im from AZ so the sun is crazy out here and my brows only held for an hour, i was looking for a gel to hold them down since my eyebrows are a little thicker so most gels (elf, nyx) wont hold them. Wouldn't recommend if you have more brow hair or thicker brow hair.

reviews.headline: Does not hold
reviews.comments: I was recommended to get this by an ulta worker to help hold my eyebrows in place and shape them but this product did not work for me. I would even use a lot of the product to hold them and they wouldn't stay a whole day. Even setting my face after with setting spray my eye brow shape would fall out of place because product couldn't hold them when I was setting my face. Really disappointed because of how pricey it was :(

reviews.headline: Perfection!
reviews.comments: Was hesitant to buying it, should have bought it sooner! Just what i was looking for. Holds brows in play with very little product.

reviews.headline: Perfect for my needs
reviews.comments: I got this in a bundle, didnt think I would use it much since I have a bad history with brow gel. However this product doesnt leave a white cast and keeps my brows in place all day, whether im at work or outside!

reviews.headline: Melts
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this so much and did for maybe a month then if melted.. in the winter! I stored it properly and everything then  one day opened it to straight liquid. Save your money!

reviews.headline: Melts

reviews.headline: Used to be amazing, doesn't hold at all anymore
reviews.comments: I used to love this product and it used to hold the brows in place all day. It was more waxy and so easy to put makeup on top of. The product was clear. Now the product is foggy and more gel like. It does not hold brows at all, honestly completely pointless to use, and brow pencils do not go well on top of it. My brows have been looking awful ever since I got a new one. I even bought another one, just in case it was a fluke. Unfortunately, it is a poor formula change. Will be switching brow products immediately!

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: I had a hard time using the product in the beginning, it would leave my eyebrows ashy and or looking white. But after speaking with an Anastasia mk-up representative at the mall, she suggested to put the product on before I put on anything.

reviews.headline: Not worth it at all!
reviews.comments: I decided to try this brow freeze wax because it went viral and I needed something to hold my eyebrows. I heard a lot of good reviews about this eyebrow wax, so i decided to give it a try despite the price. Once I used it, my eyebrows never stayed in place. The product would not hold my eyebrows in place and i have thick eyebrows. I definitely wasted my money. It is not worth it at all!

reviews.headline: It's okay
reviews.comments: I still use it because i like how it makes my eyebrows look when i first put it on but i do relaize that it donest hold my eybrows in place for very long and sometimes (not everytime) it does flake. I also think that it might be causing the pinples in my eyebrows so be aware of that.

reviews.headline: works well
reviews.comments: looking at some of the other review pictures where people are complaining about the product turning white, that is user error! youre supposed to keep the lid on tight while ur using it, so i assume ppl are keeping it open as they do their brows. i get some on my spoolie, close it and apply to one brow. open and get some again, CLOSE IT then apply it to my other brow. its lasted me months!

reviews.headline: Super oily
reviews.comments: Thus product us extreamly oily ..i will continue to my Got2b holding spray

reviews.headline: Super oily
reviews.comments: Thus product us extreamly oily ..i will continue to my Got2b holding spray

reviews.headline: love
reviews.comments: I love the polished look this gives my brows. just can't use too much or it will build up

reviews.headline: Benefit is better
reviews.comments: Not sure why abh cant make a brow gel but this is no better than the other one

reviews.headline: Love!
reviews.comments:
I love this brow gel. I purchased the brow tool and use that to scoop it on or my finger. The tool is great to brush my brows how i liked them. I let it dry a little then add on a little brow pencil for a fuller natural look.

Holds all day. No flaking.

I do not like over done brows.

faceoff_positive.comments: By now I'm sure we have all heard of soap brows. As popular as the trend has become I was a tad hesitant being that it sounded both strange, and like a lot of work. Adding another step to my already lengthy beauty routine was of no interest to me.  I tried it with a  bar of soap and loved the look. I wasn't a fan of the time and effort it required so that was my last attempt. I have such thick coarse hair there isn't a brow gel that works. As usual Anastasia Beverly Hills saves rhe day!! Releasing "Brow Freeze" a brow styling wax in a convenient little jar with plenty of product that is safe in your makeup bag or on the go purposes. Its foolproof, and beginner friendly so don't be spooked because it seems unfamiliar. Not only does it keep brows appearance groomed and in check. It gives a natural appearance after you're done painting them on. Almost removes any excess product that we sometimes miss penciling them in. I couldnt stand the way my hairs would drag downward or sparse ones upward it drove me bonkers. I can now skip the bar of soap hassle, and still benefit the "soap brow" trend! I am so appreciative ABH nailed this one for us!  I highly recommend. Also, I wouldnt forget purchasing the ABH double sided spoolie/ spatula that cones with it. Makes an already simple process that much more convenient!
faceoff_positive.headline: Finally!!!

faceoff_negative.comments: I liked this product and it worked well. But it starts to crystallize. I have to scrape and scrape product off just to get a little bit of product to use. Overall it was a waste of money. Not sure how to prevent this from happening.
